transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Hi, thank you so much for calling Viagra at Score Blue.

Speaker 2: How can I help you today?

Speaker 1: Yes, I just need to cancel my subscription.

Speaker 2: Okay, sir, I can help you with this.

Speaker 1: Could you provide me with your full name and date of birth?

Speaker 2: Rick Spohn, S-P-O-H-N, 4-21-61.

Speaker 1: Thanks, Rick.

Speaker 2: All right, I see your prescription here,

Speaker 1: initially written back in May of 2025.

Speaker 2: Your current prescription is for the 100 milligram Viagra.

Speaker 1: Now, Rick, I'm not sure if you saw

Speaker 2: on the notes here initially, this would be back in May.

Speaker 1: This is not a subscription.

Speaker 2: You're not required or obligated to get these monthly.

Speaker 1: If you wanted, you could simply pause it,

Speaker 2: and that would allow you to call in

Speaker 1: and place orders as needed,

Speaker 2: and still keep your access

Speaker 1: to the remaining refills available.

Speaker 2: Yeah, no, I just decided to just move on at this time.

Speaker 1: So I guess when you say it's not a subscription,

Speaker 2: well, it shows up every month,

Speaker 1: and it's a direct auto-pay.

Speaker 2: That seems like a subscription to me.

Speaker 1: That's how your account was initially set up

Speaker 2: by the doctor with those low quantity

Speaker 1: of the 10 and the 100 milligrams.

Speaker 2: But you can, like I said, you can adjust it.

Speaker 1: So some patients do bi-monthly.

Speaker 2: Some patients do every three months.

Speaker 1: Some patients, like I said, do the pause.

Speaker 2: So then they can just call in

Speaker 1: and place orders when they're low.

Speaker 2: Yeah, I think just today,

Speaker 1: let's just go ahead and completely just cancel this.

Speaker 2: Okay, and so upon cancellation,

Speaker 1: would close out the prescription altogether.

Speaker 2: What that means is potentially now in 2026,

Speaker 1: if you place an order, you might see a price increase, okay?

Speaker 2: And then if the AGV comes back,

Speaker 1: or there might be a slight delay

Speaker 2: when they can fulfill your order, okay?

Speaker 1: Right now, you do have access to it by pausing it,

Speaker 2: but if you wanna cancel it, we can do that as well.

Speaker 1: Yeah, I'd like to just cancel it, thank you.

Speaker 2: Okay, okay, you got it.

Speaker 1: Just give me one moment.

Speaker 2: I'm gonna mess with the pharmacy here

Speaker 1: to confirm cancellation.

Speaker 2: Okay, you're all set.

Speaker 1: Okay, will I receive a notice or anything?

Speaker 2: Yes, sir, you will get a confirmation email.

Speaker 1: Okay, then there you go, I appreciate it.

Speaker 2: Of course, happy to help.

Speaker 1: Thank you, bye-bye.
